  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Summarizing The Build**\n\nI\'ve got it! The build now succeeds without a hitch, the applet is compiled. I\'m focusing on distilling this into a clear, concise summary, according to the communication guidelines for Simple and Complex requests.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have designed and built a mobile-first, highly interactive landing page for **Beyond Hello**, a modern social experience platform for singles in Prague. \n\nHere is a summary of the design choices and interactive capabilities implemented:\n\n### \360\237\223\261 Interactive Phone Simulator & Screen Matrix\n*   **High-Fidelity Virtual Device**: Crafted a custom CSS smartphone frame complete with a dynamic camera island, top status indicators (Wi-Fi, 5G signals, power status, and clock synced with Prague local time), and functional tactile styling.\n*   **Interactive Screen Swapping**: Designed five high-fidelity application screens: **User Profile**, **Prague Quests (Explore)**, **Active Challenge**, **Experience Invitation**, and **Match Connection**. \n*   **Dual-Way Synchronization**: Clicking the bottom navigation on the virtual mockup updates the current screen view. Furthermore, browsing the step-by-step app walkthrough on the landing page automatically syncs the simulator screen to visually demonstrate each feature.\n\n### \342\232\226\357\270\217 The Swipe Fatigue Contrast\n*   **Side-by-Side Visualizer**: Contrasted traditional, cold dating app habits (exhausting swiping lists, repetitive dry chats, awkward cafe job-interview dates) with Beyond Hello\'s warm, adventure-first philosophy (real shared challenges, instant conversational icebreakers, and memorable first meetings).\n\n### \342\230\225 Experiential Challenge Board\n*   **Teaser Mini-Game**: Showcased distinct challenge types such as *Coffee Quest*, *City Explorer*, *Taste Adventure*, and *Conversation Challenge*.\n*   **Live Icebreaker Drawer**: Implemented a functional digital card drawer for the *Conversation Challenge* where visitors can click to draw randomized icebreaker questions designed to skip boring small talk (e.g., local Prague secrets and funny expat quirks).\n\n### \360\237\217\260 \"Built for Prague\" Bento Matrix\n*   **Hyper-Local Hubs**: Designed an interactive neighborhood explorer highlighting inaugural launch districts like *Letn\303\241 Park*, *Mal\303\241 Strana Alleys*, *Karl\303\255n Bistros*, *Vinohrady Squares*, and the *Vy\305\241ehrad Fortress*.\n*   **Prague Visuals**: Integrated clean photography overlays with localized, experience-based activities for each district.\n\n### \360\237\216\237\357\270\217 Prague Founding Community Registry\n*   **Persisted Registration**: Created an active launch registration form collecting name, email, age range, gender identification, and social interests.\n*   **Dynamic Spot Counter**: Configured a live countdown beginning at `942 / 1,000` spots. Submitting a new signup increments the spot count, updates the progress bar, and builds a personalized, unique printable founding ticket (e.g., `#943`) complete with a visual mock QR code.\n*   **Live client-side storage**: Registered users persist across browser refreshes via standard LocalStorage mechanisms.\n*   **Founder\'s Admin Dashboard**: Implemented a collapsible control panel at the bottom of the registration form so you can inspect registered database rows, view active demographics metrics, or clear local mock data for demonstration purposes.\n\n### \360\237\224\224 Ambient Prague Activity Notifications\n*   **Live Toast Alerts**: Added a gentle background loop that occasionally slides up a non-intrusive activity log toast detailing mock challenges being unlocked in Prague (e.g. *\"Lukas solved the Sunset riddle at Letn\303\241 Park!\"*) to simulate a lively, highly funded startup prepping for a massive launch.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 163037173
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
